</td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Sebilis Tips?</span><hr size=1> After getting my key finally im ready to head to Sebilis but first id like to get some basic info on the zone.  If anyone has tips on grouping, pathing, where to run, where to bind, where to group at, pet control, etc etc for this zone i would greatly appreciate it.  Thanks<br>
<br>
_______________________<br>
Yizznusno Onsunzziy<br>
Level 51 ELEMANTALIST!!!<br>
&lt;Brotherhood of Vengeance&gt;<br>
<br>
Conquering Norrath one bixie at a time.... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usalashpenumbra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Salash Penumbra</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.cnsj.net/guild/10pixel.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#333333>(3/15/01 2:33:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sebilis Tips?</span><hr size=1> Don't come till 54+, stay in KC till then <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
If you do wanna come though, normal place to bind is right outside the orb. Zone in is one way, but as you're a mage you can just gate out. Zone in is also &quot;safe&quot; (unless some fool trains it) and is where most pickup groups start.<br>
<br>
Running to groups isn't too easy here unless the way has already been cleared. All froglok knights can see invis, the casters and quite a bit of otehr stuff doesn't, but there's always plenty of Knight up <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :/ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":/"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Common camps are:<br>
<br>
b1- Bridge 1 - first bidge you come to, camp is normally on the other side. Typically an exp camp.<br>
b2 - Bridge 2 - second bridge you come to, also know as nec, guard, necrosis or any combination of the 4. 2 named spawns at this camp, drop some very nice weapons for melees, often camped.<br>
b3 - Bridge 3 - third bridge you come to, like b1 really, sometimes called disco hall (cos it's the hall down to the disco <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>
zone out - This is where you can zone out, often pulled from any of the 3 bridges, but when it's crowded becomnes a camp in its own right.<br>
<br>
jail - just past b1, some ok stuff drops here.<br>
bar - a bit past jail, some better stuff drops here <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
chef - a little past bar, can take a shortcut past bar though. Some other good stuff drops here. Often bar and chef are camped together for some very nice exp.<br>
<br>
crpyt - this is behind a locked door past b2/nec/guard (rogue required). 4 named spawn here, the most notable being Heirophant Prime Grekal who drops the Hierophant's Cloak.<br>
emp - just past the crypt and often camped by the crypt group if it's strong. He drops some nice stuff and high level spells. Blood also spawns in the room before him and drop Cone of the Mystics.<br>
<br>
d1 - Disco 1 - this is the area past b3. Quite a few named in the area, great exp.<br>
d2 - Disco 2 - as above really, but the back half of it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Those are the &quot;up top&quot; areas of the zone and all can be seen on this map, study and learn!:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.eqmaps.com/mapz/oldsebilis6.jpg">www.eqmaps.com/mapz/oldsebilis6.jpg</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
<br>
There's also 2 other high level camps not on the map:<br>
<br>
king - Myconid Spore King - also called shrooms, drops a VERY nice tunic, but NEED a 58+ chanter.<br>
lower jail(?) - a jail area before the shrooms, with some very hard frogs, and a second zone out.<br>
<br>
Past those are Reets/Juggs and Trakanon himself for raiding level parties. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uyizznusnoonsunzziy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yizznusno Onsunzziy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#333333>(3/20/01 9:40:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sebilis Tips?</span><hr size=1> I must say, it is hard to get in a group at 51 in this place but it is well worth the wait!  After finally getting in a gang(lizzy necros, froglocks, and a big beetle..you know where im talking about) group we camped the place with extreme ease.  Furthermore, within a hour of camping we got two spell drops: Gift of Xev and Bristlebane's Bundle.  However, if you plan on fighting in this place(at 51), your gonna have to set aside a whole day for getting in a group and fighting, if you dont have the time...better start heading to karnors. <p>Yizznusno Onsunzziy<br>
