Doh!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uevieofvazaelle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Evie of Vazaelle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 112<br> <font color=#333333>(6/12/01 10:02:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sebilis Tips?</span><hr size=1> yeah seb is awesome for exp.  I spent 2 weeks here and went from beginning of 54 to 56.  Very hard to find groups if you're not 54+.  Gotta keep pet on a tight leesh, use summon companion whenever you can.  Beware of the pathing in disco, it's one of those round rooms with 2 entrances. :P  And one thing I've noticed in seb, whenever you get an add, it hits the mage!  I think it's some sort of sick joke or something I have a hotkey that says &quot;add on me&quot;.  All the other mages I've talked to say the same thing so it's not just me honest! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   drops here are dissapointing but what do you expect... we can use about 4 things that drop here in normal exp grind groups, froggie robe (disco), heiro cloak (crypt) (if a melee nbgs and wants to roll for this whack him/her upside the head kk) rod of anihilation, some stupid 10 int 2hb water staff that clicks enduring breath.  This place absolutely kicks ass for exp tho.<br>
<br>
 <p>[56 Conjurer] Evie (Human) <<a
href="http://www.promethianorder.com">Promethian Order</a>>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukalamos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalamos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 86<br> <font color=#333333>(6/13/01 8:39:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Seb and Mages</span><hr size=1> Funny you mentioned that Evie .. I noticed that as well.  I was in the Chef last night and it seemed that every add would come and whack me first ... no matter where I was standing or if I was sitting or not.  There was one add that came through the door that passed our sitting Cleric and walked THROUGH the melees attacking the current target to come smack me.  I was like WTF?!?!?!?  Happened on more than one occasion.  Maybe Seb MOBs are smarter and know to try and take out the biggest threat to them .. us Mages!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Needless to say I keep Phantom Armor up all the time when hunting in Seb due to the fact that I know I'll be taking a beating from time to time.<br>
